        {
            "decision": "CT ABDOMEN AND PELVIS: ABDOMEN:  There are several subcentimeter hypodense lesions in both lobes of the liver.  These are too small to accurately characterize by CT.  The left hepatic duct and common hepatic and common bile duct are moderately dilated down to the level of the sphincter of Oddi.",
