        },
        {
            "decision": "MRI Pelvis w/ and w/o contrast: Large, heterogeneously enhancing, multilobulated mass within the pelvis, with central areas of necrosis and focal hemorrhage. Given its large size, its relationship to adjacent structures is difficult to discern. However, it appears to displace, rather than arise from, the uterus. ",
            "category": "Category 7: Evaluating test result",
            "start_offset": 5864,
            "end_offset": 6176,
            "annotation_id": "NU_048"
        },
        {
            "decision": "It is intimately associated with and inseparable from a distal loop of small bowel. Given this relationship to the small bowel and its appearance, this is thought most likely to represent a small bowel GIST. ",
            "category": "Category 7: Evaluating test result",
            "start_offset": 6178,
            "end_offset": 6384,
            "annotation_id": "NU_049"
        },
        {
            "decision": "While neither ovary is seen, this is thought less likely to be ovarian in origin given only the trace amount of free fluid and no evidence of metastatic disease within the pelvis.",
